Troubleshooting
Common Issues:

Elasticsearch won't start: Check Java installation and memory settings
Logstash parsing errors: Verify file paths and permissions in configuration
No data in Kibana: Ensure Logstash pipeline is processing files correctly
Permission denied: Run CyLR with sudo for system file access
Debug Commands:

# Check service logs
sudo journalctl -u elasticsearch -f
sudo journalctl -u logstash -f

# Verify file permissions
ls -la cylr-data/
sudo chmod -R 644 cylr-data/

# Test Elasticsearch connectivity
curl -X GET "localhost:9200/_cluster/health?pretty"
